
Task
How many bears outweigh one elephant?
The mass of one bear is equal to bearWeight. The mass of one elephant is elephantWeight. What is the smallest number of such bears that can outweigh an elephant?
Write a function called bears that takes the numbers bearWeight and elephantWeight as arguments and returns the smallest number of bears that can outweigh one elephant.
Examples:
• the bears (300, 5000) function must return 17;
• bears (250, 5150) should return 21.

Solution
function bears (bearWeight, elephantWeight) {
return Math.ceil (elephantWeight / bearWeight);
}
